have been put around...</i>


979
01:13:19.580 --> 01:13:20.581
Prick.

980
01:13:20.660 --> 01:13:22.628
<i>Supermarkets in 23 major cities.</i>

981
01:13:22.700 --> 01:13:25.829
<i>Most supermarkets in the country
still stock grapes.</i>


982
01:13:25.900 --> 01:13:29.143
<i>But a significant number of shoppers,
mostly housewives,</i>


983
01:13:29.220 --> 01:13:30.426
<i>are not buying the grapes.</i>

984
01:13:30.500 --> 01:13:32.582
<i>They are observing the boycott.</i>

985
01:13:32.660 --> 01:13:36.551
<i>That's a report from Delano, California.
This is Charles Walker...</i>


986
01:13:48.100 --> 01:13:52.071
We know that your organization supported
us in the picket lines in Pittsburgh,


987
01:13:52.140 --> 01:13:53.187
and we were wondering if you could

988
01:13:53.260 --> 01:13:56.104
organize another team of people again
this coming week.


989
01:13:56.180 --> 01:13:57.944
What city are you in?

990
01:13:58.020 --> 01:13:59.101
Montreal?

991
01:13:59.180 --> 01:14:01.581
Wisconsin is next, okay?

992
01:14:01.660 --> 01:14:02.946
Okay, I'll tell everyone.

993
01:14:03.580 --> 01:14:04.820
Thank you, bye.

994
01:14:08.140 --> 01:14:10.746
Last report estimates that we've cost them

995
01:14:11.180 --> 01:14:13.581
$17 million to date!

996
01:14:18.300 --> 01:14:20.587
I wish they'd paid that in fair wages.

997
01:14:21.340 --> 01:14:25.061
What is your view
of the strike of the grape industry?


998
01:14:25.140 --> 01:14:26.426
The grape boycott...

999
01:14:26.500 --> 01:14:30.027
Well, I've classified that
in the past in a number of public occasions


1000
01:14:30.100 --> 01:14:32.467
as immoral. I think it is.

1001
01:14:33.540 --> 01:14:35.110
Get me John on the phone!

1002
01:14:35.180 --> 01:14:36.181
Yes, sir.

1003
01:14:45.180 --> 01:14:46.420
Did you see it?

1004
01:14:47.260 --> 01:14:48.830
Man of the year!

1005
01:14:49.180 --> 01:14:50.909
I thought they were going to make
him Pope.


1006
01:14:53.260 --> 01:14:55.911
I know... It's all right.

1007
01:14:57.500 --> 01:14:59.264
Well, let's get together on Sunday.

1008
01:15:04.540 --> 01:15:06.827
I saw her last week.
She told me and I forgot.


1009
01:15:07.980 --> 01:15:10.824
But she looks great. 
She looks great.

1010
01:15:10.900 --> 01:15:11.947
Yes, she does.

1011
01:15:12.020 --> 01:15:13.624
Gentlemen.

1012
01:15:15.020 --> 01:15:16.021
Look,

1013
01:15:17.060 --> 01:15:20.109
I say it's time for the families to
put their differences aside


1014
01:15:20.900 --> 01:15:22.948
and speak together with one voice.

1015
01:15:23.340 --> 01:15:24.341
I agree.

1016
01:15:25.540 --> 01:15:28.589
Let's sit down with these bastards
and settle this thing once and for all.


1017
01:15:34.260 --> 01:15:35.625
Jack, are you serious?

1018
01:15:35.700 --> 01:15:38.067
You want to sit down with these characters?

1019
01:15:39.700 --> 01:15:41.270
We can't hang on much longer.

1020
01:15:41.700 --> 01:15:43.748
This boycott is bleeding us to death.

1021
01:15:44.300 --> 01:15:48.350
If we sit down with them it won't
be a boycott, it will be an insurrection.


1022
01:15:49.580 --> 01:15:50.991
We still gotta negotiate.

1023
01:15:51.060 --> 01:15:54.781
We don't have to negotiate,
we have to dictate terms.


1024
01:15:55.740 --> 01:15:56.741
Look,

1025
01:15:58.100 --> 01:16:00.023
I hate dealing with these dirty foreigners,

1026
01:16:01.100 --> 01:16:03.910
but we can't keep
putting on fake labels forever.


1027
01:16:04.820 --> 01:16:06.709
I'm a dirty foreigner, Jack.

1028
01:16:09.540 --> 01:16:10.587
You know what I mean.

1029
01:16:11.260 --> 01:16:13.388
I'm not the only
one who feels like this.

1030
01:16:14.900 --> 01:16:17.790
You're not? Well, who else feels that way?

1031
01:16:18.860 --> 01:16:20.271
Jack's got a point.

1032
01:16:20.780 --> 01:16:25.422
It's time for us to cut our losses
and negotiate.


1033
01:16:25.940 --> 01:16:27.988
You don't negotiate with children.

1034
01:16:28.060 --> 01:16:31.542
You don't give children
every piece of candy in the store.


1035
01:16:32.260 --> 01:16:36.982
With children, you set the rules
and you make sure they obey them.


1036
01:16:45.140 --> 01:16:46.141
How you been?

1037
01:16:46.740 --> 01:16:49.505
I'm good. I broke 70.

1038
01:16:54.380 --> 01:16:57.021
You know, when the Chinese
came to America to build the rail roads,


1039
01:16:57.140 --> 01:16:58.981
you know what
they demanded of their overseers?


1040
01:17:00.100 --> 01:17:01.101
No.

1041
01:17:01.420 --> 01:17:03.821
Food. Good food.

1042
01:17:05.620 --> 01:17:06.985
And enough time to enjoy it.

1043
01:17:07.980 --> 01:17:10.460
And if the owners skimped on that,
they wouldn't lift a finger.


1044
01:17:11.900 --> 01:17:13.902
Give the Chinese a good meal every day

1045
01:17:13.980 --> 01:17:16.141
and they could
build the infrastructure of a continent.


1046
01:17:17.500 --> 01:17:20.424
Their meal is what gave
their lives dignity.


1047
01:17:21.700 --> 01:17:25.182
And to them, dignity was
more important than money.


1048
01:17:26.220 --> 01:17:28.268
That's nice, huh?

1049
01:17:28.980 --> 01:17:31.711
You have this annoying habit
of turning everything into a lesson.


1050
01:17:33.820 --> 01:17:35.390
I just like Chinese food.

1051
01:17:40.380 --> 01:17:41.461
How you doing?

1052
01:17:43.060 --> 01:17:44.824
I told you. I'm good.

1053
01:17:46.500 --> 01:17:48.070
With golf?

1054
01:17:48.900 --> 01:17:50.106
What's wrong with golf?

1055
01:17:55.500 --> 01:17:57.628
You are becoming a real American.

1056
01:17:59.300 --> 01:18:00.790
Golf is from Scotland.

1057
01:18:08.940 --> 01:18:12.342
<i>We interrupt to bring
you this bulletin from Los Angeles.</i>


1058
01:18:12.420 --> 01:18:15.788
<i>New York Senator Robert Kennedy
has been shot in the head,</i>


1059
01:18:15.860 --> 01:18:18.431
<i>minutes ago as he left the platform</i>

1060
01:18:18.500 --> 01:18:21.549
<i>from which he made his victory statement
in Los Angeles.</i>


1061
01:18:21.620 --> 01:18:24.863
<i>The detailed report
which we did receive initially</i>


1062
01:18:24.980 --> 01:18:28.985
<i>pictured Kennedy
on the floor of the hotel kitchen.</i>


1063
01:18:29.060 --> 01:18:33.110
<i>Blood streaming from his face,
his eyes open but unseeing.</i>


1064
01:18:33.580 --> 01:18:36.390
<i>He is on his way,
or perhaps has already arrived</i>


1065
01:18:36.460 --> 01:18:38.747
<i>at an unnamed hospital in Los Angeles.</i>

1066
01:18:39.700 --> 01:18:44.183
<i>The moment further word is received
we will pass it along to you immediately.</i>


1067
01:18:46.020 --> 01:18:50.150
<i>The final act in the
stunning tragedy of Robert Francis Kennedy</i>


1068
01:18:50.220 --> 01:18:52.222
<i>began this morning
with a touching ceremony</i>


1069
01:18:52.340 --> 01:18:55.549
<i>in St. Patrick's Cathedral
here in New York City.</i>


1070
01:18:55.620 --> 01:18:58.351
<i>The late senator was then
transported to his final resting place,</i>


1071
01:18:58.940 --> 01:19:02.786
<i>near his brother the late President
at Arlington National Cemetery.</i>


1072
01:19:05.220 --> 01:19:08.508
<i>I, Richard Milhous Nixon,
do solemnly swear...</i>


1073
01:19:11.220 --> 01:19:13.507
Everyone, stop working for a minute.

1074
01:19:13.900 --> 01:19:16.983
Come, join the strike.
Cesar Chavez wants to defend you!


1075
01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:22.744
<i>That I will faithfully execute the
office of President of the United States...</i>


1076
01:19:27.380 --> 01:19:29.781
<i>And will to the best of my ability...</i>

1077
01:19:32.300 --> 01:19:34.587
<i>Preserve, protect and defend...</i>

1078
01:19:36.740 --> 01:19:39.584
<i>The Constitution of the United States...</i>

1079
01:19:47.060 --> 01:19:48.789
<i>So help me God.</i>

1080
01:20:25.100 --> 01:20:27.148
Slow down!

1081
01:20:27.620 --> 01:20:30.146
Slow down! Slow down!

1082
01:20:37.460 --> 01:20:40.623
- Call an ambulance!
- Juan! Juan!


1083
01:20:42.060 --> 01:20:43.664
Help! Help!

1084
01:21:12.220 --> 01:21:14.746
<i>We thank you
for all that you are doing for us.</i>


1085
01:21:14.820 --> 01:21:16.584
<i>We very much appreciate it.</i>

1086
01:21:17.460 --> 01:21:18.461
Yes, sir.

1087
01:21:18.540 --> 01:21:20.508
Well, you're someone
who understands business


1088
01:21:20.580 --> 01:21:23.823
and you're a Californian,
we're all Californians here...


1089
01:21:24.340 --> 01:21:25.671
Yes, sir.

1090
01:21:26.380 --> 01:21:28.030
I'll do my best.

1091
01:21:28.100 --> 01:21:30.467
And thank you, thank you so much.

1092
01:21:31.980 --> 01:21:33.789
Take care, bye.

1093
01:21:35.620 --> 01:21:39.261
Nixon has promised
to sell our grapes in Europe.


1094
01:21:39.380 --> 01:21:40.791
And whatever's leftover

1095
01:21:40.860 --> 01:21:44.148
he'll have the Department of Defense
buy and feed to our soldiers.


1096
01:22:06.940 --> 01:22:08.351
<i>They're getting you
out in five days,</i>


1097
01:22:08.420 --> 01:22:10.229
but I'm not sure about the others.

1098
01:22:10.300 --> 01:22:11.711
It's all lies.

1099
01:22:12.220 --> 01:22:13.710
They're saying we provoked them.

1100
01:22:13.780 --> 01:22:17.068
That the strike is not legal, they are
painting us to look like criminals.


1101
01:22:17.260 --> 01:22:20.503
And ever since they dumped the grapes
in Europe, their sales have gone up there.


1102
01:22:23.660 --> 01:22:25.230
By 140%.

1103
01:22:35.620 --> 01:22:37.429
We're not gonna survive Nixon.

1104
01:22:43.260 --> 01:22:44.625
Then we have to go over there.

1105
01:22:46.700 --> 01:22:47.906
To Europe?

1106
01:22:49.980 --> 01:22:52.347
If they're running, we have to catch them.

1107
01:22:53.660 --> 01:22:56.140
We can barely keep things together here,
Mansi.


1108
01:22:56.220 --> 01:22:57.301
I know.

1109
01:23:19.820 --> 01:23:22.420
I never thought
I'd be saying this in my life.


1110
01:23:25.220 --> 01:23:28.349
To Richard Milhous Nixon!

1111
01:23:28.820 --> 01:23:30.026
To Nixon!

1112
01:23:45.340 --> 01:23:48.150
Focus on human law,
since it actually exists over in Europe.


1113
01:23:48.260 --> 01:23:50.706
The growers have completely
subverted the system here,


1114
01:23:50.780 --> 01:23:52.703
but Europe still defends workers' rights.

1115
01:23:52.780 --> 01:23:55.220
- - I hear they
get one month vacations there.


1116
01:23:55.740 --> 01:23:57.265
You might want to mention that

1117
01:23:57.340 --> 01:24:00.184
Vietnam is basically awash
in Bogdanovich's grapes and napalm.


1118
01:24:00.260 --> 01:24:01.989
I heard the food is terrible over there.

1119
01:24:02.060 --> 01:24:05.109
I don't care how bad the food is,
you're not starting a fast, Cesar.


1120
01:24:05.180 --> 01:24:06.261
Where is my coat?

1121
01:24:15.300 --> 01:24:16.461
<i>CESAR". Hey, Helen.</i>

1122
01:24:16.580 --> 01:24:18.309
You should see this place.

1123
01:24:18.580 --> 01:24:19.991
How are the kids?

1124
01:24:21.340 --> 01:24:22.580
And Fernando?

1125
01:24:25.380 --> 01:24:26.381
Okay.

1126
01:24:26.540 --> 01:24:29.020
<i>I'll see you in a couple of days.</i>

1127
01:24:30.380 --> 01:24:31.427
Fares please.

1128
01:24:31.700 --> 01:24:32.747
Yes, sir.

1129
01:24:32.820 --> 01:24:33.941
- Albert.
- 2p please.


1130
01:24:55.500 --> 01:24:57.867
- Mr. Chavez?
- Yes.


1131
01:24:58.900 --> 01:24:59.947
Lovely to meet you.

1132
01:25:00.060 --> 01:25:01.346
- Nice to meet you.
- Welcome.


1133
01:25:07.940 --> 01:25:10.261
We're here with Cesar Chavez,
the civil rights activist,


1134
01:25:10.340 --> 01:25:13.105
who has caused quite a stir in America
from his ongoing boycott


1135
01:25:13.260 --> 01:25:16.230
<i>that has meant millions of Americans
have stopped eating table grapes.</i>


1136
01:25:16.300 --> 01:25:17.426
Does that work for you, Mr. Chavez?

1137
01:25:17.540 --> 01:25:18.701
Thank you.

1138
01:25:21.260 --> 01:25:23.580
<i>We are making a plea
of common sense, to an industry</i>


1139
01:25:23.620 --> 01:25:26.783
<i>that refuses to recognize
the basic human rights of its workers.</i>


1140
01:25:26.940 --> 01:25:30.023
<i>Besides this boycott,
your movement has marched and striked</i>


1141
01:25:30.100 --> 01:25:32.307
<i>and you yourself have
done a 25 day fast.</i>

1142
01:25:32.420 --> 01:25:33.581
<i>Why has it gone this far?</i>

1143
01:25:33.740 --> 01:25:37.631
<i>Well, despite the success we had
against the growers in California,</i>


1144
01:25:38.300 --> 01:25:40.382
<i>they still refuse
to sit down and negotiate with us.</i>


1145
01:25:41.220 --> 01:25:43.461
And it's not
a question of economics anymore.


1146
01:25:44.660 --> 01:25:46.230
<i>It's more a stubbornness.</i>

1147
01:25:46.460 --> 01:25:48.667
<i>They want to show that
they're strong and not weak.</i>


1148
01:25:48.780 --> 01:25:50.384
<i>So they would
rather export the grapes</i>


1149
01:25:50.460 --> 01:25:51.985
<i>than sit down and negotiate with you?</i>

1150
01:25:52.300 --> 01:25:55.065
They'd rather sell their grapes to London,
or Stockholm


1151
01:25:55.260 --> 01:25:58.343
and think that that will erase all
the indignities that people have suffered.


1152
01:26:00.100 --> 01:26:02.660
<i>And what kind of support have you
received here in Great Britain?</i>


1153
01:26:02.820 --> 01:26:06.029
Here in Britain, we have the Transport and
General Workers Union support,


1154
01:26:07.300 --> 01:26:09.302
<i>and they have endorsed our boycott.</i>

1155
01:26:11.980 --> 01:26:13.982
<i>The dock loaders refuse to unload grapes.</i>

1156
01:26:14.300 --> 01:26:15.381
What are you saying to me now?

1157
01:26:15.460 --> 01:26:17.349
Wait a minute! 
We had a deal!

1158
01:26:17.460 --> 01:26:19.827
Which is a great endorsement
of our boycott.


1159
01:26:20.980 --> 01:26:24.985
<i>We're optimistic to have
similar support from other countries.</i>


1160
01:26:25.140 --> 01:26:29.304
<i>Diverse religious groups throughout the
continent have shown their support.</i>


1161
01:26:29.460 --> 01:26:32.589
<i>Even the Pope has agreed to meet us.</i>

1162
01:26:32.660 --> 01:26:35.140
I've got them grapes
halfway through the Atlantic.


1163
01:26:37.300 --> 01:26:38.461
Hello?

1164
01:26:38.820 --> 01:26:40.504
So, what are you hoping to achieve?

1165
01:26:43.340 --> 01:26:44.671
<i>Well, it's never been
about the grapes.</i>


1166
01:26:44.740 --> 01:26:46.101
<i>It's always been about the people.</i>

1167
01:26:46.300 --> 01:26:48.826
<i>The poorest of the poor, the marginalized.</i>

1168
01:26:49.220 --> 01:26:50.506
<i>The ones who have been ignored.</i>

1169
01:26:54.220 --> 01:26:56.826
<i>There would be no food on the table
without these people.</i>


1170
01:27:01.020 --> 01:27:04.547
<i>And these people have
names, faces, families.</i>


1171
01:27:07.700 --> 01:27:11.022
<i>And I guess what we want to accomplish
is to give these people a voice.</i>


1172
01:27:20.700 --> 01:27:23.829
<i>But will this be enough,
considering the amount of resistance?</i>


1173
01:27:24.660 --> 01:27:26.708
Once social change begins,

1174
01:27:27.740 --> 01:27:29.265
it can't be reversed.

1175
01:27:30.940 --> 01:27:33.386
<i>You can't uneducate someone
who has learned how to read.</i>


1176
01:27:35.060 --> 01:27:38.223
<i>You can't humiliate someone
who has pride.</i>


1177
01:27:43.740 --> 01:27:47.028
You can't oppress someone
who is not afraid anymore.


1178
01:27:48.060 --> 01:27:50.028
We have seen the future
and the future is ours.


1179
01:27:58.580 --> 01:27:59.581
Ready?

1180
01:29:03.460 --> 01:29:04.461
Don't answer it!

1181
01:29:04.660 --> 01:29:05.707
I'm right here.

1182
01:29:06.180 --> 01:29:09.548
Don't take three hours.
I have to drop this off.


1183
01:29:23.620 --> 01:29:24.667
What's wrong?

1184
01:29:25.460 --> 01:29:26.507
They want to sign.

1185
01:29:27.220 --> 01:29:28.221
Who?

1186
01:29:28.660 --> 01:29:32.062
All of them. All
the growers want to sign.

1187
01:30:03.860 --> 01:30:05.862
It's an interesting day
you choose to be late.


1188
01:30:07.220 --> 01:30:09.109
Come on, they are waiting inside.

1189
01:30:48.380 --> 01:30:51.101
You have to admit,
this old Croat put up a hell of a fight.


1190
01:30:51.780 --> 01:30:55.421
Yeah, I can do that, as long as you can
admit this little Mexican kicked your ass.


1191
01:31:00.900 --> 01:31:02.580
<i>Brothers and sisters of the fields,</i>

1192
01:31:04.780 --> 01:31:07.431
<i>all around us were those
who said it could never be done.</i>


1193
01:31:09.100 --> 01:31:12.627
<i>People said that
the growers were too powerful,</i>


1194
01:31:15.220 --> 01:31:16.904
<i>the police would be against us...</i>

1195
01:31:18.660 --> 01:31:20.469
And the courts would beat us down,

1196
01:31:21.780 --> 01:31:22.780
and that sooner or later

1197
01:31:22.820 --> 01:31:25.824
we would fall back into the poverty
and despair of our forefathers.


1198
01:31:26.500 --> 01:31:27.786
But we didn't!

1199
01:31:29.780 --> 01:31:30.941
We didn't

1200
01:31:31.740 --> 01:31:33.185
because our common suffering

1201
01:31:34.180 --> 01:31:36.467
and love for each other kept us together.

1202
01:31:39.980 --> 01:31:41.630
Five years we were on strike!

1203
01:31:45.180 --> 01:31:48.423
It kept us sacrificing and fighting
for a better tomorrow,


1204
01:31:49.580 --> 01:31:51.503
a better tomorrow that we all dream about

1205
01:31:52.300 --> 01:31:54.462
as we work among these beautiful vines.

1206
01:31:56.100 --> 01:31:59.149
And when millions and millions of
Americans stopped doing one thing,


1207
01:31:59.980 --> 01:32:01.186
eating grapes,

1208
01:32:02.300 --> 01:32:03.790
we won the strike!

1209
01:32:04.380 --> 01:32:05.541
We won!

1210
01:32:11.580 --> 01:32:13.070
Yes, we can!

1211
01:32:58.820 --> 01:33:01.710
<i>I know there is no way
to justify the things that I've done...</i>


1212
01:33:02.380 --> 01:33:04.189
<i>Or that I've not done for you.</i>

1213
01:33:05.020 --> 01:33:06.909
<i>It saddens me to think that</i>

1214
01:33:07.220 --> 01:33:09.541
<i>we never got a chance
to go fishing together</i>


1215
01:33:10.340 --> 01:33:12.104
<i>or catch a baseball game</i>

1216
01:33:12.780 --> 01:33:14.384
<i>or even go watch a movie.</i>

1217
01:33:16.380 --> 01:33:18.348
<i>There's no way to turn back the clock</i>

1218
01:33:19.060 --> 01:33:20.391
<i>and to make up for lost time.</i>

1219
01:33:22.780 --> 01:33:23.861
<i>But I want you to know that</i>

1220
01:33:23.900 --> 01:33:26.187
<i>your mother and I
miss you very much, Fernando.</i>


1221
01:33:28.180 --> 01:33:29.909
<i>It seems so ironic to think that,</i>

1222
01:33:30.020 --> 01:33:33.388
<i>because I've tried to do things that
my father could never do for us,</i>


1223
01:33:34.420 --> 01:33:36.070
<i>I'm now so distant from you.</i>

1224
01:33:38.780 --> 01:33:41.750
<i>Please know that
the day you came into this world</i>


1225
01:33:41.860 --> 01:33:44.466
<i>was also the day that I
received the clarity</i>


1226
01:33:45.260 --> 01:33:46.989
<i>that I so desperately needed.</i>

1227
01:33:48.900 --> 01:33:50.709
<i>You and your brothers and sisters</i>

1228
01:33:51.420 --> 01:33:53.149
<i>are the purpose for my struggle.</i>

1229
01:33:54.100 --> 01:33:55.590
<i>Everything I do is for you.</i>

1230
01:33:56.780 --> 01:33:58.623
<i>And I hope you remember that.</i>

1231
01:33:59.940 --> 01:34:02.420
<i>I also hope that one day</i>

1232
01:34:03.220 --> 01:34:05.826
<i>you can be as proud of
me as I am of you.</i>

1233
01:34:42.020 --> 01:34:43.988
<i>But I want
more than anything else,</i>


1234
01:34:44.060 --> 01:34:45.505
<i>I would like to see the poor</i>

1235
01:34:47.780 --> 01:34:50.511
<i>take a very direct part in shaping society.</i>

1236
01:34:50.620 --> 01:34:52.190
<i>And let them make the decisions.</i>

1237
01:34:52.980 --> 01:34:56.507
<i>And in our case, if the poor are not
involved, then change will never come.</i>